'''David Clendon''' is a New Zealand politician and member of the [[Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand]]. Following the resignation of [[Sue Bradford]], Clendon will become a Member of the New Zealand Parliament on 30 October.

==Political Involvement==
In both the [[New Zealand general election, 1999|1999 elections]] and the [[New Zealand general election, 2005|2005 elections]] Clendon polled third in the seat of [[Waitakere (New Zealand electorate)|Waitakere]].

Clendon was the [[Party Chair|co-convenor]] of the [[Green Party of Aotearoa New Zealand|Green Party]] from 2001 to 2004.

In the [[New Zealand general election, 2008|2008 general elections]] Clendon stood as a candidate in the [[Helensville (New Zealand electorate)|Helensville electorate]], coming third with 5.96% of the electorate vote, with [[Prime Minister of New Zealand|Prime Minister-elect]], [[John Key]], winning the seat.

